args:
When the party finds an ancient piece of gear
called a mana kiln in the facility, Ed suddenly
attacks them. Afterward, Phares appears and
informs the group of Ed's true identity: Beren,
the fifth scion of Alberia. The stunned group
then pursues the pair deeper in the complex.
I've seen a lot of strange things in my day,\nbut this place is creepin' me the hell out.
Yeah, this place is WEIRD, man.

The materials used in its construction are
unknown to me. I suspect this structure is
the reason Lake Reeve was shut off from
the rest of the world.
I dunno, but it came from inside the ol'\nspooky palace there. Guess we gotta go\ninside now whether we want to or not.
Don't leave my side, Ed. Understand?
I know I ain't the sharpest arrow in the\nquiver, but I got NO idea what any of\nthis junk is.
I, too, am befuddled, Luca. Perhaps they\nare some manner of magical weapon\nlike those we saw in Chanzelia.
Step aside for Ranzal the narrator!\n...Nope. Never mind. I can't make\nheads or tales'a all them squiggles.
By Ilia... This is Ancient Alberian.

Perhaps. Some of the Church's earliest
sacred writings are in Ancient Alberian,
and I studied the language during my
early years there.
So get to translating already!\nWhat's it say?!

A moment please, Notte. Hmm...
Yes, this one here reads ＂mana kiln,＂
while these two are ＂collection spout＂
and ＂regulation valve.＂
Ya wanna translate that translation there?
I heard tales of mana kilns long ago.

They are devices that absorb natural mana
in order to create a kind of artificial mana.
However, I have never seen one with
my own two eyes before this day.
It's gotta be REALLY old if you've never\nseen it, Cleo! ...Er, no offense.
Which means this facility is a remnant of\na civilization even more ancient than the\nformer Dyrenell Empire.

The pact between the Goddess Ilia and the
Holywyrm Elysium dictated that all mana-
related technology made by mortal hands
was to be disposed of.
Guess they missed this one.\nStill, what the hell is it doin' here?
It's okay, we'll find him together.\nJust come back here, all right?
You are the hollow prince of the Alberian\nroyal family, {player_name}...
And soon you will be broken.
Get away from him, Your Highness!\nThis fiend is his doing!
I thought his speech and attitude strangely\nphilosophical for a child of his age.\nWho are you, demon?! Speak!
Aw, hell. The kid's usin' black mana!
Who are you, Ed? Who are you REALLY?!
Ah, I was wondering what all the fuss\nwas about. It seems my guests have\nfinally arrived.
You did well to make it this far, Brother.\nAh, but how rude of me. I haven't made\nproper introductions yet!
Beren, what are your first impressions\nof dear {player_name}?

He is quite the fortunate prince indeed.
A happy, naive man who believes in
his convictions without the slightest
shred of doubt.
You say that like it's a bad thing, dude!\nNothin' wrong with a little self-confidence.
Enough games, Phares. Who is this child?
I should think you familiar with the\ntale of Alberia's fifth scion, yes?\nThe one who disappeared?
The name of the lost prince was Beren.\nAnd this child...is our brother.
Wait a sec. Waaaait, wait, wait. This is\n{player_name}'s older brother?!
He can't be! Look how tiny he is!
Is your world so simple that you trust\nonly what your eyes behold?
Aw, c'mon! Ya really think we're all dumb\nenough to fall for this happy horsecrap?!
I merely speak the truth. Whether you\nbelieve or not is no concern of mine.
Are you really my brother, Beren?
My father... Leonidas... All they ever said\nwas that my older brother went ＂missing.＂
A story purely for appearances sake.\nYou ought to cultivate a greater ability\nto tell truth from fiction, my brother.
They hid his existence. They took the\ngreatest secret of the Alberian royal\nfamily and tried to simply wish it away.
Ah, excellent! The mana kiln has\nfinally reached maximum output.
You've come at a perfect time, Brother.
We shall wait for you at the\ninnermost chamber.
Come on, everyone!\nWe have to find them!
